<div class="col two-sm last" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn2">
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Travel information</h3>
    Rail informationTake the Intercity service to Darlington. There is a taxi rank outside Darlington Railway Station. The hospital is one and a quarter miles away.<br/>Local directionAccess from the north and south is via the A1(M) exiting at junction 58 onto the A68 sign posted Darlington. Travel two and a quarter miles then turn left into Hollyhurst Road. The hospital's main entrance is on the right. You may park in the Visitor's Car Park. Please note this is a Pay and Display car park. <br/><br/>Road informationFrom the A1 / A1(M), follow sings for the town centre or A68.  The hospital is sign-posted from the town centre.  For all routes follow the signs from the town centre.Bus informationClick the travel Website link below to access the full list of available travel options from Darlington Borough Council.  Most buses to Darlington Memorial Hospital leave from stand H at the top of Tubwell Row or stand L towards the bottom of Tubwell Row.


</div>
</div>
</div>
